Vibe Coding Logs: GridFit Project

Project: GridFit - Smart Gym & Body Recomposition App
Role: Frontend Engineer & System Architect
AI Assistant: Claude 3.5 Sonnet / GPT-4 (or replace with your actual model)
Date: April 2024

Note: This document tracks the primary AI prompts used to generate the core structural and functional components of the GridFit application. The methodology follows a "Vibe Coding" approach, starting with UI/UX shells and progressively building complex logic and state management.

Prompt 1: Core Layout & iOS-Style Navigation

Intent: Generate the foundational mobile-first UI shell, navigation mechanics, and global styling variables.
Output Component: index.html (Base structure), switchView() routing logic, Bottom Tab Bar.

Prompt:
"Act as an expert frontend engineer. Create a mobile-first, iOS-style web application layout using strictly vanilla HTML, JS, and Tailwind CSS (via CDN). Include a bottom tab bar with 5 icons (Summary, Live Gym, Matrix, Coaches, Plan) using Lucide Icons. Implement a smooth view-switching logic in JavaScript so only one main view is visible at a time. The overall theme should be dark mode (#000000 background) with glassmorphism effects (backdrop-blur)."

Prompt 2: Body Recomposition Matrix & Chart Generation

Intent: Build the core logic for body calibration (M1-M3, F1-F3) and dynamically translate physiological goals into actionable workout data visualizations.
Output Component: #view-vector section, calculateWithScalars() algorithm, Chart.js integrations.

Prompt:
"Create a 3x3 grid component for selecting body types (ranging from Lean/Slender to High Mass/Stocky). When a user selects a 'Baseline' and a 'Target', calculate a workout split (Resistance Training vs Cardio percentage). Use Chart.js to render these results dynamically into two charts: a doughnut chart for the 'Macro Split' and a bar chart for the 'System Focus' (Z1, Z2, HIIT, METCON). Provide separate theme colors for Male (Blue) and Female (Pink) modes."

Prompt 3: Dynamic Coach Booking System

Intent: Generate the interactive coach scheduling UI, handle nested view transitions, and manage booking state logic.
Output Component: #view-coach, #view-coach-detail, coachSchedules JSON structure, booking state management functions.

Prompt:
"Design a coach booking view. First, display a list of coaches with their avatar, name, and specialty tags. When a coach is clicked, transition to a detail view showing a horizontal scrollable calendar for the next 7 days. When a date is clicked, reveal a grid of available time slots. Add logic to handle 'Booking' and 'Canceling' sessions, updating the state in localStorage and reflecting the booked status on the home dashboard."

Prompt 4: Immersive Workout Timer

Intent: Add a full-screen, focused state for live workout tracking with visual feedback.
Output Component: Full-screen modal overlay, timer interval logic, state update functions.

Prompt:
"Build a full-screen, immersive workout timer overlay hidden by default (z-index 100). When triggered via a JavaScript function startWorkoutTimer(category, title, color), animate the overlay into view. It should display a large pulsing ring, the elapsed time (MM:SS), and a 'Finish' button. When 'Finish' is clicked, log the elapsed minutes to a global state variable and hide the overlay."
